PROTON PUMP INHIBITORS (PANTOPRAZOLE, OMEPRAZOLE, LANSOPRAZOLE, ETC) are a medication not intended to be taken longer than 2 months (8 weeks) to treat ulcers. Evidence shows that they can contribute to pneumonia, depression, osteoporosis and death. Recommendation is to take ZANTAC (RANITIDINE) or PEPCID (FAMOTIDINE) for heartburn, in addition to avoiding heartburn foods like coffee, chocolate, tomatoes, onions, and spicy or sugary foods.